								<p>Orifold is free and open source, so builds aren't notarized by Apple yet. One-time first launch:</p>
								<p><b>macOS 14:</b> right-click Orifold → Open → Open.</p>
								<p><b>macOS 15:</b> open Orifold once (it's blocked), then System Settings → Privacy &amp; Security → <b>Open Anyway</b> → password.</p>
								<p>Prefer zero dialogs? Install with Homebrew below — it handles Gatekeeper for you.</p>
							</div>

							<details class="details">
								<summary>Other ways to install</summary>
								<div class="chip-cmd" style="margin-top:0.8rem">
									<code>brew install --cask orifold</code>
									<button type="button" class="copy-btn" data-copy="brew install --cask orifold" aria-label="Copy Homebrew command">
										<Fragment set:html={icoClipboard} /><span class="copy-btn-label">Copy</span>
									</button>
								</div>
								<p class="fine-print" style="margin-top:0.8rem">
									Or the direct <a href={rel.zipUrl}>.zip</a>. <a class="arrow-link" href={rel.allReleasesUrl}>All releases<span class="arrow-ico-wrap"><Fragment set:html={icoChevron} /></span></a>
								</p>
							</details>
						</div>

						<div class="dl-dev" data-reveal style="--d:1; min-width:0">
							<h3>Build it yourself</h3>
							<div class="term-card">
								<div style="overflow-wrap:anywhere"><span class="prompt">❯</span> git clone {site.repoUrl}.git</div>
								<div><span class="prompt">❯</span> cd Orifold</div>
								<div><span class="prompt">❯</span> ./scripts/install-mac.command</div>
							</div>
							<div class="pet" data-pet="ori">
								<span class="fig pet-arrive-target">
									<span class="pet-anim" set:html={oriTwitch} aria-hidden="true"></span>
									<img class="pet-poster" src={`${base}/assets/ori-figure.svg`} width="104" height="104" alt="" aria-hidden="true" />
								</span>
								<p class="bubble">Doubt me? Build it yourself.</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>
			<hr class="crease-line" />

			<!-- Paper fortune spotlight: the page's closing delight. SSR renders a real
			     first fortune (no-JS and pre-hydration visitors get a real line); the
			     inline script shuffles on click and gently auto-refolds while the section
			     is on screen. All bursts are finite and reduced-motion safe. -->
			<section id="fortune-fold" class="fold fortune-fold" aria-labelledby="fortune-eyebrow">
				<div class="ff-decor" aria-hidden="true">
					<span class="ff-glow ff-glow-a"></span>
					<span class="ff-glow ff-glow-b"></span>
					<span class="ff-dot ff-dot-1"></span>
					<span class="ff-dot ff-dot-2"></span>
					<span class="ff-dot ff-dot-3"></span>
					<span class="ff-dot ff-dot-4"></span>
				</div>
				<div class="wrap">
					<div class="fortune-card" data-reveal>
						<span class="ff-aura" aria-hidden="true"></span>
						<span class="ff-pets" aria-hidden="true">
							<span class="ff-pets-glow"></span>
							<span class="ff-pet ff-pet-gami" data-pet="gami">
								<span class="guide-fig" set:html={gamiWag}></span>
								<img class="guide-poster" src={`${base}/assets/gami-figure.svg`} width="96" height="96" alt="" />
							</span>
							<span class="ff-pet ff-pet-ori" data-pet="ori">
								<span class="guide-fig" set:html={oriTwitch}></span>
								<img class="guide-poster" src={`${base}/assets/ori-figure.svg`} width="96" height="96" alt="" />
							</span>
						</span>
